The paper presents a non-parametric Bayesian model for extracting hidden factors over observed data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The model has a deep learning structure, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. The paper also mentions applications in wireless networks, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. Additionally, the use of the Metropolis-Hastings method for inference suggests that it may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The paper also deals with continuous values for hidden factors and weights, which suggests that it may belong to the cs.SI (Signal Processing) sub-category. Finally, the use of non-parametric Bayesian methods suggests that it may belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
